'From Squeak2.8alpha of 12 January 2000 [latest update: #2040] on 26 April 2000 at 10:23:42 pm'!"Change Set:		SymbolPrintingTweaksDate:			26 April 2000Author:			Dan IngallsCleans up a couple of non-fatal problems with recent changes to the printing of symbols:1.  The system category shown in HierarchyBrowsers (caught by Scott Wallace).2.  The array structure proffered by the 'reorganize' command for class and system organizations."!!ClassOrganizer methodsFor: 'printing' stamp: 'di 4/26/2000 20:22'!printOn: aStream 	"Refer to the comment in Object|printOn:."	| elementIndex |	elementIndex _ 1.	1 to: categoryArray size do: 		[:i | 		aStream nextPut: $(.		(categoryArray at: i) asString printOn: aStream.		[elementIndex <= (categoryStops at: i)]			whileTrue: 				[aStream space; nextPutAll: (elementArray at: elementIndex).				elementIndex _ elementIndex + 1].		aStream nextPut: $); cr]! !!HierarchyBrowser methodsFor: 'initialization' stamp: 'di 4/26/2000 20:20'!systemCategorySingleton	| cls |	cls _ self selectedClass.	^ cls ifNil: [Array new]		ifNotNil: [Array with: cls category]! !